      "type": "html",
      "text": "<i>Perhaps now is the time for me to reflect a bit on [[Wiki Reductionism]], since the initial hot emotions seem to have cooled a little (especially my hot emotions). In the weeks leading up to the Reduction, there was a lot of talk on Wiki on how Wiki was growing too fast, how pages were getting too large, how [[Thread Mode]] and [[Wiki On Wiki]] were getting out of hand. It appeared to me that the \"general consensus\" was that people should [[Refactor Faster Delete More]], but that there was a taboo on deletion which prevented this. But nobody made any attempt to actually break this taboo. So I decided to do what everybody was talking about and \"reduce\" a couple of pages. (By the way, I only deleted about 5 pages, of which I put back 2 when urged to. I mostly deleted content added by myself.)</i>",
